    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** providing our highest offensive floor, boasting an elite 82.97 efficiency score. His matchup against Chris Bassitt is bolstered by a significant +16% park factor and a strong BvP history, making him our primary engine for Runs and RBI. Similarly, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** earns a massive +19% boost from his favorable matchup against Matt Waldron\u2019s 7.83 xERA; as we prioritize stolen bases, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** remains a high-upside play despite his lower lineup position, as his speed profile is essential for our weekly category goals. **Junior Caminero** also projects well, landing in the \"Strong\" tier at 74.22 by leveraging an advantageous platoon look against the right-handed Williams.\n\nOur toughest lineup decision involved **Colt Keith**, who finished just outside the starting nine with a 46.51 score. While his projection benefited from a move to the #3 spot, the optimizer ultimately pivoted to **Caleb Durbin** and **Luke Raley** to maintain structural balance, as **Colt Keith** struggled to overcome the negative SP skill coefficient against JR Ritchie. We are closely monitoring the 40% rain risk hovering over the contest featuring **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber**. While **Trea Turner** remains a \"must-start\" due to his elite speed and the +4% stolen base boost he receives against Logan Webb\u2019s slower delivery, any further weather degradation could force a late-game pivot for our MI and OF slots. We proceed with **Gary Sanchez** and **Kazuma Okamoto** at their respective positions, both of whom land firmly in the \"Strong\" tier despite pending lineup confirmations.",
